    &lt;CommentText&gt;Dear RB-34,  
We really appreciate that you have taken the time to give us this feedback, especially as you are just going home with your little one, thank you very much for this.  
As you say room 6 does not have any natural light into it and the skylight requires changing, this has been requested but firm chasing will now take place. I am hearing from you how stressful it was to be in that room with an unwell little one in an uncomfortable environment.Thank you for telling us of this unacceptable situation, I will ensure that the correct teams are made aware of this so that the work can take place. We will need the correct length of weather to be able to change the skylight in the roof. it would be good to know if you feel the wall colour should be changed to a bright welcoming colour, please let us know. I will also ensure that there is always the opportunity to have a fan to cool down if needed as we know the hospital environment can be very warm.  
Thank you so much for this feedback, please have my assurance that we will take this forward.  
Suzanne Pilkington  
Matron for Children's Services.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
